title: For Sale:  Beretta 92G w/ (3) magazines & holster
postcontent:
This pistol is an ex-police model, and shows some holster wear from being carried.  It has Trijicon night sights, dated 2002, which still glow dimly but are replaceable if desired.  I used this pistol for IDPA competition for a few months before I moved on to a custom Beretta, and it performed well.  I've replaced the stock hammer spring with a Beretta 'D' spring, which lowered the double-action and single-action trigger pull weight.  Except for the custom 92 which I'll be keeping, this 92G has the best trigger of any of the 92 series pistols I've owned.  

I'll be including (3) 15-rd genuine Beretta magazines and a DeSantis Yaqui Slide belt holster with the pistol.  The holster retails for just under $50, and here is a link to it: http://www.desantisholster.com/store/SEARCH-BY-GUN-MANUFACTURER/BERETTA/92F-92FS-M9/BELT-HOLSTERS/Yaqui-Slide

Some background info:  

While the 92FS practically grows on trees in terms of availability, the 92G is a variant that many people haven't heard of or seen before.  On the 92FS, the lever on the slide acts as a decocker and will also latch downwards into an "on safe" condition.  That same lever on the 92G is springloaded and doesn't have a "safe" position.  The reason for this is that the safety can be accidentally engaged while racking the slide on an FS variant, and certain agencies didn't want this to be possible in the middle of a gunfight.  The G variant actually uses a different slide than the FS, and safety/decocker parts don't interchange between the two.  Beretta didn't make the G variant commonly available to the public because of liability fears, so they're hard to come by.  Their most popular usage today is for self defense by shooters "in the know," and for action shooting use where the lack of a safety means one less thing that can go wrong in a fast-paced competition.   

LOCATION / SALE INFO: 

I'm located about an hour west of Charlottesville in the Harrisonburg area. It's often easiest for me to meet at the Mt Crawford Park and Ride off I-81 Exit 240 if that's convenient for you.

Price is cash only. I'm not interested in shipping in connection with Armslist ads, so please don't ask. People who ask anyway will be ignored, as I've already answered the question in the sentence before this one. Legal face-to-face sales to VA citizens only, so please have your driver's license with you. If I get a bad vibe about you, no sale -- simple as that.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson M&P Shield 40 9mm Barrel Holsters Ammo Grips
postcontent:
This pistol is in excellent condition, well taken care of and kept clean and lubed with less than 400 rounds down the (40 S&W) barrel. Included is a never fired factory S&W 9mm barrel that can be dropped into the 40 Shield to convert it to a 9mm Shield instantly. I have tested this with my brother's Shield and this conversion is well documented on the internet. These barrels are very sought after and now practically impossible to find since you can no longer order one from S&W. They've restricted the sale of these once people caught on to the simple conversion that pretty much gives you two guns in one. Now the only way to obtain one is to send your 9 Shield in to Smith with a faulty barrel for them to replace. The following video proves that the barrels are identical in every aspect except bore diameter. The 40 mags will be able to load 9mm cartridges with room for one more round than the 40 S&W cartridges. Being able to shoot both calibers gives you more options and can save you money at the range since 40S&W ammo is more expensive than 9mm. 

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=flnFIzI6MIw&feature=share&list=TL0M6XeB3NonM

Also included are three 6 round flush mags, there is no extended mag that would normally come with a Shield. I traded for a 6 rounder and then bought an additional 6 rounder because I found they were easier to conceal and I actually had a more positive grip when I held the Shield with the flush mags. 

Two holsters included, DeSantis Insider Black Leather IWB and Uncle Mike's Reflex Holster OWB - both top quality 

Also throwing in a Pachmayr Tactical Grip Sleeve makes a huge difference in terms of positive grip, less felt recoil and better accuracy.

Shield has three dot sights painted with Glow-On gun sight paint that is more durable, glows bright in the dark, and stands out better than original low quality white paint that the three dots come with out of box. Most Shields end up with the factory white dots falling out of the dot holes after so many rounds.

Stamping on the frame and 40 barrel has been painted silver.

Also included is a 20 round box of Speer Gold Dot 40 S&W - best defense ammo imo

And a like new Smith & Wesson Extreme Ops Folding Knife:
http://www.sportsmanswarehouse.com/img/products/original/smith_and_wesson_extreme_ops_folding_knife_1306315_1_og.jpg

I'm the original owner and purchased this firearm in March for $490 out the door.

I'm far from desperate so any low ball offers will be ignored, and I love this pistol so the only way I'd let all of it go is to get a lot of what I paid for back out of the deal. The barrel is worth $200 easy.

Asking $800 or best offer for everything or $600 or best offer without the 9 barrel. Original box, lock and papers all included, email me with a phone number and I can shoot you a text. Must sign bill of sale. Would consider a partial trade for boxed 9mm ammo (no hand loads)

postcontent:
$775 or best offer. Stainless HK USP V1 .45 (full frame) with two 10rd mags, original box and manual, one box (20 rounds) Hornady Critical Defense ammo and Blackhawk Serpa holster. Great shooting gun. Buyer must have a valid CCW permit or NC purchase permit. 

Originally designed for the American market the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever a combination safety and decocking lever is frame mounted and quickly accessible unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

title: For Sale/Trade:  HK P2000 .357sig DA/SA w/6 mags
postcontent:
HK P2000 .357sig DA/SA w/6 mags 
100-150 rounds fired

The first of the many recent additions to the Heckler & Koch handgun line, the P2000 and incorporate features of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with the latest innovations of HK engineers. A refinement of a design created for several European police agencies, the P2000 is available with a traditional double-action/single-action trigger mode and the LEM/CDA (Law Enforcement Modification, also known as Combat Defense Action) trigger system first introduced in 2001 on the USP Compact "LEM" model.

The HK Law Enforcement Modification trigger system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull from first to last round fired) with a double-action hammer system.

Developed especially for a U.S. government agency, the Law Enforcement Modification (or LEM for short), is a unique trigger mechanism created specifically to improve the trigger performance and reduce the weight of the Double-Action Only (DAO) trigger pull on HK pistols.

With this mechanism, HK pistols can be fired like a standard DAO semi-automatic pistol where every round is fired by simply pulling the trigger fully rearward with the hammer starting at the forward rest position. The design of the proprietary HK LEM system allows the weight of the DAO trigger pull to be reduced to a smooth and constant 6.18 - 8.5 pounds (27.5 - 37.8 N) because the two-part hammer is pre-cocked every time the slide moves rearward. Trigger pull on conventional double action pistols is 12 - 15 pounds (53.4 - 66.7N).

The unique LEM pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. Optional adjustment (by HK certified armorer) can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.

Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation — one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the P2000. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single action pistol.

A set of simple-to-install modular grip panels allow the P2000 to be custom-fitted to any shooter’s hand. An ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers make handling the P2000 natural and easy for right and left-handed shooters alike.

Industry standard mounting rails allow the widest variety of lights, laser aimers, and accessories to be added to the P2000 by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 includes the same recurved, hook trigger guard found on the USP Compact and uses reliable and widely available USP Compact magazines.

A limited edition P2000 German Police Model features a "closed" accessory mounting rail system and a tapered trigger guard.

Available in 9 mm and .40 S&W.
P2000 variants available in the USA (all supplied with three additional back straps)

title: For Sale:  Laguiole En Aubrac folding pocket knife
postcontent: Very nice hand made LaGuiole En Aubrac folding knife with a leather sheath. I learned a lot about these knife this weekend after talking to a family member of this French company who lives here in Albuquerque. First of all this part of France is known for knife making and there are a lot of LaGuiole marked knifes that come from this area that are well made. But there are a lot of Chinese and Pakistani knockoffs out there. This knife was made by a 5th generation knife maker whose whole family has worked for LaGuiole En Aubrac. Each maker puts his own design on the knives and this man and the 4 men before him uses feathers. The attention to detail on this knife is amazing and you really need to see it. The first makers of these knives were sheep herders and they were Catholic and they put Shepard s crosses in silver nails in the handles.

title: For Sale:   Fine Moore 7 Shooter Revolver .32 caliber
postcontent:
serial #3869
 Fine Moore 7 Shooter Revolver  
This is a 7 shot revolver with a 6 inch octagonal barrel in 32 rimfire caliber. These were made in the early 1860’s and I have owned numerous examples inscribed to Civil War officers. They were very popular before manufacturing stopped due to the Rollin White patent infringement suit won by Smith & Wesson against numerous firearm companies. The silver plated brass frame is beautifully hand engraved with scrollwork and retains about 30% of the silver plate. The cylinder and barrel retain some of the original factory blue finish. The barrel is marked “D. MOORE. PATENT. SEPT, 18. 1860.” A very fine example.
